12/08/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Unknown assailants threw a firebomb at the Turkish consulate in Thessaloniki early on Thursday (August 12th). No injuries were reported. Government spokesman George Petalotis described the incident as a "criminal act" and condemned it. "We express our sorrow to the Turkish government," he said in a statement, adding that "those responsible will be arrested and brought to justice." (ANA-MPA, Hurriyet, AFP - 12/08/10)
